President Cyril Ramaphosa is addressing opposition parties to discuss the national response to the COVID-19 disaster. On Sunday Ramaphosa declared a national state of disaster following the outbreak of the coronavirus in the country. • Editor’s note: This livestream has ended. Watch the recording above. PARLIAMENT - President Cyril Ramaphosa will meet with leaders of political parties in Parliament on Wednesday to discuss the national response to COVID-19. The meeting is part of a series of consultations the president is undertaking with leaders across various sectors of society amid the COVID-19 pandemic. READ: South Africa's coronavirus infections escalate to 85 Ramaphosa has declared the coronavirus pandemic a national state of disaster in terms of the Disaster Management Act. Meanwhile, Parliament is taking precautionary measures against the coronavirus and will be suspending business indefinitely as from Wednesday. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp.